Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.05,0:04:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Taru, come on! Taru-Taru-Taru! Taru! Taru! \N- Just let me wash my face!{guess, I think it's doushite there, the rest - no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.89,0:04:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen here, Taru.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.26,0:04:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad just gave me a map to the treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we look for it together?{/it's for us to find it}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure hunt? \NSounds exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.52,0:04:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But this map is kinda convoluted, \NI can't make heads or tails of it.{/difficult, I don't understand it well}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.34,0:04:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask Tama-chan, she may advise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.05,0:04:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Brilliant, Taru! \NI'm counting on you!{most likely this, but unsure, may be "you've become quite the reliable ally" or "you can count on me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If we find the treasure, you'll also get a share \Nbiiiig enough for a life of luxury!{/to splurge/brag your wealth}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.58,0:04:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll eat takoyaki until you're full!{/eating as much takoyaki as you like}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.00,0:04:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat takoyaki until full?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:05:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure hunt begins!{/this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.17,0:05:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait for me, Taruruuto!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.07,0:05:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,First - head north-northwest!{/take a course/direction}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.66,0:05:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait, I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.14,0:05:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.02,0:05:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What a doofus!{/like a fool}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.22,0:05:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You must still be half-asleep \Nto believe in something like a 5-billion-yen treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.89,0:05:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Iyona-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.05,0:05:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I think treasure hunting \Nis a very inspired thing to dream of.{/it's totally okay to dream about something like ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.12,0:05:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, would you look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.80,0:05:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not tasting any of my hospitality \Nonce I find the treasure!{/when I ... you won't get a treat}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That was dangerous! Open your eyes!{/be careful}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.28,0:05:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yo, Iyona-san. If you happen to go out, \Nlet me be your guide to the city, will you?{/Why won't you let me show you around If you happen to go out? - unsure if he means this or "you, please show me around" or just "please let me know/announce it to me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Harako! Who in the world figured it'd be a good idea \Nto let an elementary school student drive a car?!{/you think it's okay for you, a ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.45,0:06:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Aged appearance is a useful asset.{/one of the privileges of looking old/having face of a full-grown}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.06,0:06:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if someone finds out, the head of the \NHarako Conglomerate, my papa, will hush things up.{/if it leaks, I'll just ask papa to cover everything up}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.39,0:06:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, what are you up to, \Nequipped like that?{/where are you going looking/dressed like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.25,0:06:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, you should hear this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.92,0:06:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd believe you even if you tell them?!{I think its 誰がお前なんかに教えるもんか but it makes no sense lit is "who's going to teach you" and the best I can suppose is "who told you this"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.01,0:06:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru desecrated my maiden's lips!{/stole my first kiss! - pretty wild guess, i assume it's otomeno/na kuchibiru which is just "girl/maiden's lips" but I think this is implied} {yume: "Honmaru ga otome no kuchibiru wo...!" with the verb omitted. From context: "Honmaru touched my lips!", she's upset at being grabbed like that. \N      Any implications of a kiss here would be a real stretch though.\N      I'm inclined to words this as "He just touched my lips!" into "The hell is your problem?!"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.62,0:06:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I did {\i1}what?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.89,0:06:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going treasure hunting!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.72,0:06:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. Got a map here. \NTreasure - pile of coins and stones!{/lots of coins and jewels}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.05,0:06:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Lemme see...{ closer}{/where, where?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.27,0:06:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Look closer.{/here, you can look}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.04,0:06:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, baby!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.88,0:06:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona-san, we'll meet again soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Map snatched...{/taken away}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.51,0:07:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Taruruuto...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.27,0:07:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.61,0:07:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For crying out loud! \NWhat are we to do now?{/why do you keep doing this}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.13,0:07:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's just an incorrigible goof.{/they'll do stupid things for eternity}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Little to see here.{/let's leave them alone} Let's go, Iyona-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.73,0:07:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just that, you handed the map over to Harako!{/of all things, you gave harako the map}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.36,0:07:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it, move!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.91,0:07:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Rui-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.52,0:07:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost both the treasure and Iyona-chan \Nin a course of one day!{/left without ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.54,0:07:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru! All thanks to you!{/it's your fault}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.08,0:07:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Honmaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.12,0:07:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.26,0:07:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I memorized the location marked on the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? You did? That's just big!{/splendid/great}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.06,0:08:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're overdoing it, Taru!{/grew up too much}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.02,0:08:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! We need to cross the mountain \Nbefore Harako does!{kosu is both cross over a mt/beat/surpass/come so may be any of those}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.36,0:08:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that... just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.41,0:08:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, lend me your ear.{surprisingly, this is literal, although "give/move closer" works too}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.19,0:08:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Came up with an even better idea, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.71,0:08:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Soari-ri-ri-ring!{rather "leap/pounce/break free"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.14,0:08:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, if we fly, get there faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.58,0:09:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold up there, Taru! \NYou can't just leave me behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.83,0:09:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, if you flap{/move} your ears, you fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.87,0:09:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do that on my volition!{I think he means "I can't flap my ears voluntairly/don't have faculty for this" and not "I can't fly if I move my ears"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.29,0:09:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a telltale reflex \Nof twitching your ears when it's money you're after.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.43,0:09:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunting for treasure. 5 billion. I'm after the money!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.38,0:09:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.69,0:09:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, impressive!{/doing well}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.19,0:09:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Money!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.40,0:09:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Money! I'm as light as ever!{/much lighter this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.90,0:09:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.00,0:09:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we there yet, Taru?{/is it still far}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.42,0:09:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru-chan, past that mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.64,0:09:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here, Honmaru.{/arrived}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.96,0:09:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That mountain, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Harako's goons!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.93,0:10:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Young Master, the express \Narchaeological analysis has shown that...{/Young Master, the immediate \Nmining site inspection has shown...} {this middle part is boggling my mind, is sounds as koukou gakusei but why'd they ask a high school student do it, a bit like houkoku but that's a weird place to place "report" in, most likely it's kouku gokusei - specially issued on mining site, but then again, how is mining site related to the investigation of the map and the report?}{/without wasting any time, the mining area specially made investigation results are...} {Yume: Bocchama, sassoku koukogakusha ni shirabesasemashita kekka" -> "Young Master, the express archaeological analysis has shown that..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{the results testify that }This drawing is, without a doubt, \Nan authentic and accurate map of the place.{/a real thing, as the inspection has shown}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.85,0:10:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This discovery is sure to cause a sensation.{/this indeed seems like a great discovery}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.44,0:10:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure hunting in my leisure time? \NWould do for a diversion.{/that is an interesting thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.52,0:10:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Taruruuto, if we mess around any longer, \Nhe'll beat us to it!{/if we are slow, we is going to overcome us/leap ahead of us}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.37,0:10:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave this to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,~Sneak Peek!~
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.96,0:10:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Found!{/there it is}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.36,0:10:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And treasure is...{/where is treasure?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.47,0:10:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Taru! \NLet me see it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.47,0:10:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten minutes passed already?{unsure, maybe he means "this one expires in 10 mins as well"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.97,0:10:53.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H362684&\blur1\3c&H8787AB&}Garbage! \N{\c&H2B211D&}Don't throw it here!{this is literal and idk why they didn't just write "garbage disposal is prohibited" or smt}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.85,0:10:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, help!{/save me}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Incorpore-re-re-real!{/Immateri-ri-ri-rialize!/become a ghost!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.94,0:11:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic for passing through things, \Nbrought us straight to the place.{/we arrived to the good place}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.71,0:11:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, we made a clean landing!{maybe we're lucky or we arrived or even let's go, I think the joke here might just be that tsuiteru is also "stick/attach" and honmaru is covered in dirt}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Clean {\i1}what{\i0} now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.21,0:11:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru stinky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.48,0:11:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.27,0:11:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get your stinky on me!{again, kutsukeru is attack/stick together so I think he means "don't get near me/don't stain me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.43,0:11:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What can this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.12,0:11:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't touch things haphazardly!{/without thinking}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Broke{/fell} off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.46,0:11:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is serious,{/bad/serious} Taru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:11:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.44,0:12:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In the movies I've seen, these kinds of places \Nare always full of traps{/mechanisms} protecting the treasure!{/in such cases, there are devices ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.66,0:12:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't touch any...{/touching things may be grave}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.00,0:12:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Too late now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.11,0:12:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Run for your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.48,0:12:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you waiting for, Taru?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Can takoyaki grow that big, too?{correct is "I want to eat takoyaki that big" but I'm unsure whether he thinks it's a takoyaki or just compares it to one}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.61,0:12:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Cretin!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.24,0:12:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Taruruuto! Next time you'll think twice \Nbefore touching strange stuff!{/it's because you grope weird things on your own volition/selfishly}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.21,0:12:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A dead end...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.84,0:13:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nowhere else to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.45,0:13:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru! Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.37,0:13:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It turned the other way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.94,0:13:23.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs30\bord3\b1\fade(500,0)\c&H362C28&\blur0.5\3c&H268577&}Repeller{斥 - push away}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Attractor, when you cast a spell of "Taru," \Nbecomes Repeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.01,0:13:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Repeller pushes away anything you command it to{/the designated object}.{the word is rather to push aside; to thrust aside; to brush aside; to throw off; to shrug off (e.g. pressure)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.42,0:13:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're saved...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.74,0:13:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, the treasure hunt continues!{/let's go ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.50,0:13:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Tama-chan, please direct us to the treasure.{/guide us to where the treasure is}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.97,0:13:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing, Taru-chan.{/I understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.46,0:13:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Start by passing through this wall.{/first, make your way past that wall}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.89,0:13:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! It's here!{/this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.37,0:13:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you know. Turns out, \Nthat boulder was driving us in the right direction? Gee...{/so it was a good thing we hurried to run away this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:13:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh, Taru.{/this taru guy}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.87,0:13:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! Why the wait?{/what's the matter}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.15,0:14:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Where did you go, Honmaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.17,0:14:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.82,0:14:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What now, been here all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.18,0:14:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After me, hurry!{/faster, come!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.73,0:14:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.06,0:14:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! You should tread carefully, \Nthere's a water basin that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.35,0:14:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Very timely!{/too late}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.13,0:14:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, more of deadly mechanisms \Nmight hide beyond every corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.65,0:14:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Be cautious, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.28,0:14:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Worries aside! \NWe'll be A-Okay, Honmaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.21,0:14:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru! You triggered something again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.18,0:14:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, you cretin!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.92,0:14:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Trunsform!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.35,0:15:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure hunting is{/looks} fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Good Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Puffed you up!{it seems it's a sound of puffing out your cheeks}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.55,0:15:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.79,0:15:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.66,0:15:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.23,0:15:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we not in the treasure room yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.15,0:15:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Stre-re-retch!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.88,0:16:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This was fun, Honmaru! \NLet's hunt treasures more often!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.97,0:16:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What part of it was {\i1}fun{\i0}, exactly?{/where did you see fun here}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.95,0:16:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now I thought I'd be a goner because of you!{/due to your fault, I thought I'd die} \NLearn to self-reflect at least a bit!{/start contemplating a little, you!/learn some shame/regret}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.58,0:16:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru, you did it again...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.70,0:16:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.17,0:16:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're screwed. \NNow we're for real darn screwed!{lit is smt like "you're that kind of man/you're really that stupid" so I dunno what exactly he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.79,0:16:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Honmaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Young Master, \NI regret deeply to inform you of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.71,0:16:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears we still are unable \Nto locate the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:16:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Obtaining a goal without any opposition \Nis devoid of excitement.{/if it would have been easily found, I would have lost the interest}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.43,0:17:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, it's about time \Nto start playing trumps.{/for the leading actor makes an appearance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.26,0:17:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.28,0:17:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru-chan, the treasure room is in front of you.{/deeper in/in the inner part}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.34,0:17:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally!{/did it}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.49,0:18:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,My treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.08,0:18:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Who dares to intrude, \Nsnatching away the treasure?!{/ encroaching on}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.76,0:18:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the treasure's guardian!{/watchman}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No tomb raider shall leave this place alive!{/thieves cannot return home alive}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.02,0:18:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.53,0:18:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what for...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.12,0:18:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're done now...{/nothing can be done now}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.83,0:18:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I have treasure? Can I?{/please give me the treasure - choudai has a strong treat/gift tone, implying she would do it willingly}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.37,0:18:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Rub, rub.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.04,0:18:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think of it, \Nmy lifetime was still so short.{/looking back, it was a brief life}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.42,0:18:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I don't have a choice.{/can't help it, it seems}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.88,0:19:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I can't decide{/grant} such matters on my own.{/we won't tell anyone else about it, okay?}{unsure, jijou is circumstances; conditions; situation; reasons; state of affairs so I think she means "mind you, I have my personal reasons for that" but maybe even she means "but that's only because I have a lot of other errands to run"; most likely it's "I can't just let you have it your way, there are many factors"} \NThough I'm not giving you the treasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.28,0:19:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. You should make do with this.{/endure/restrain yourself to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.22,0:19:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The seeds that grow into a money tree.{lit: seeds of a tree that is to become money}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru! Got the goods!{/I was given a good thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.51,0:19:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What a... Nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.07,0:19:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Auntie, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.32,0:19:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,See you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.12,0:19:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful on your way home!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.62,0:19:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Auntie" is what I least expected...{lit is "except I'm not aunt" - most likely she means "I'm too young to be called that" but maybe, and her vampire teeth suggest that too, she implies she is not his aunt but some other taru's relative}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.53,0:19:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All's well that ends well, Honmaru.{/we we lucky}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.90,0:19:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry home \Nto plant those money tree seeds right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.59,0:19:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Though not 5 billion, \N1 billion is good enough, too!{/5 bil was out of question/impossible, so we return with about one bil}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.93,0:19:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Harako!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.09,0:19:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure obtained.{/I got the ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.20,0:19:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.98,0:20:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Property deed, belongs to Harako Conglomerate.\NYoung master bought this mountain, you see.{/the land here was bought by ..., in other words, this is bocchan's property}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.07,0:20:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot take away anything that lies in this land. \NThat would be larceny, otherwise.{/stealing}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.78,0:20:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Or would you prefer us \Nto hand you over to police custody?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.73,0:20:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Tree that bears money?{/money tree}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.62,0:20:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Even more of it for me?{rather, it's something like "I earned/made profit today"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.64,0:20:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.59,0:20:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One billion... \NNo, I wouldn't have minded even just 100 million.{/would have been happy ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But now all of that just turned into a flat 0.{/But now everything is down the drain.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, cheer up. \NBesides, you not hungry yet?{I hope its 腹減った but unsure, also unsure if he is asking "are you not hungry?" or just says he is hungry}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.42,0:20:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to be the always-carefree-Taruruuto.{unsure, I think it's "in whatever mood you are, you're good"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.37,0:20:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Taru-chan! Honmaru-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.85,0:20:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.57,0:20:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad I found you!{unsure what is chouda here, choudai is "give/receive/eat" but ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.10,0:20:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been so curious about what happened after,{/been constantly wondering what are they up to now} \Nand was on my way to your house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.47,0:20:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, was it fun, Taru-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.83,0:20:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw many interesting things, Iyona.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:20:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.36,0:20:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. They are my first home-made ones.{/I was trying to make them at home, so.../although ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.95,0:21:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Takoyaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.43,0:21:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Having grown branches so heavily laden{ with ripe fruit} \Nin a matter of just few hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.93,0:21:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No less from the treasure of Jamatai kingdom{usually id do it "riches" but here it doesn't fit so well}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This should serve as an indisputable proof \Nthat money circulated in the form of stones then{/in ancient times}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.40,0:21:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is certain to cause a sensation!{/this is a great discovery}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.82,0:21:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it's a bit of an overkill \Nto call it money-bearing tree.{/is a bit overblown a name.}{I think he means "that is well said/rich of someone to call it a money tree" but unsure}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.70,0:21:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya friggin kidding me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.02,0:21:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooops.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.41,0:21:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Young Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.37,0:21:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.75,0:21:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So tasty, Iyona. \NYour takoyaki are the best.{/thanks for the ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.99,0:21:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Taru-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.67,0:21:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Honmaru, Iyona's takoyaki \Nis even better than the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.37,0:21:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And Honmaru-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.31,0:21:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Deli-li-licious!{/totally tasty}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.17,0:21:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.94,0:22:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right, Taruruuto.{/that's right}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.79,0:22:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The takoyaki that Iyona-chan put her heart in,{/made, putting her whole heart in} \Nand that cute sincere smile...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.60,0:22:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We stumbled upon a treasure way more precious \Nthan that found in any crypt!{/got our hands on the most amazing of all the treasures}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.91,0:22:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Delicious! Irresistibly delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.65,0:22:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Taru?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.40,0:22:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Iyona, make takoyaki again sometime. \NPromise me, promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.91,0:22:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I always considered the hotcakes my forte.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.59,0:22:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hotcakes are fine, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.95,0:22:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nay!{/no way} Takoyaki, takoyaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.25,0:22:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Taruru!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.30,0:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I earned the disgust of Iyona-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Ijigawa! \NAll because of her pranks again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.12,0:22:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? If you got something to tell me, \Nthen put it frankly, you bed-wetter! {umeroyaro - no clue what is it, but idc bc jikai}{Yume: このおまる野郎 -> lib. "You bratty shithead". Up to the editor's discretion here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My patience is on its last legs! \NTaruruuto!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.00,0:22:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A magic punishment. \NYou can count on my help!{/I will cooperate}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.19,0:23:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Magical Taruruuto-kun:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.67,0:23:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Ijigawa Rui.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.67,0:23:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Every-ry-ryone, watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.67,0:23:06.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 7 \NI am Ijigawa Rui\N{(ijigawarui = malicious)}
